The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Siva to help Lankan spin
Chennai, July 12 (PTI): Former India leg-spinner Laxman Sivaramakrishnan will assist Sri Lankan spinners at a three-day camp in Colombo starting Tuesday. Sivaramakrishnan, a member of the BCCI spinners committee, will interact with Sri Lankan coach John Dyson. Thanking BCCI president Jagmohan Dalmiya for granting him the permission to accept the Lanka offer, Sivaramakrishnan said he was confident of helping the aspiring spinners all over the world solve their problems.  Copyright 
